reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for car rides!!
reviews.reviewText: We have this attached to our Doona so it works great when our baby riding in the stroller version or when she’s in the car. It keeps her eyes busy and she loves the little sounds it makes. Reasonably priced, would recommend!! The black and white contrast is perfect for baby eyes!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Baby loves it and I love how baby gets occupied
reviews.reviewText: Baby loves to work at his motor movements with this. It sparks his curiosity and occupies him enough for me to make a quick meal and eat it. It’s versatile enough to not only go In the car seat but anything with an arm like his gym set, the side of his crib, the arch over his bouncer, and even on a tension rod if need be. It’s durable and somewhat easy to travel with. Unfortunately it’s. It very easy to clean since the toys do not detach. My little loves the toys and is still trying to figure out how each toy works. Although it’s a great distraction, he enjoys it more when we interact with him and his toys to figure out everything about the toy. This is worth the buy! I will add, it’s not long enough for him to grab and pull to his mouth to teethed so I really wouldnt call it a teething toy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute and washable
reviews.reviewText: It’s cute, well made and durable toy. I love the sounds. I washed it in a laundry machine in cold water and then dried in a dryer a couple of times on a delicate regime. All the sounds work after drying! I tried handwashing first but unsuccessfully bc it is really hard to wash the detergent out.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Cute but needs improvement
reviews.reviewText: I bought the snake that is meant to wrap around the car seat handle. The hanging toys are cute. I like the design of this. The snake needs a little more stretch to it so that the toys can hang evenly and the ties at each end of the snake are way too short and it is hard to tie them to the car seat handle for this reason.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Baby loves it but it’s too small
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. My little guy LOVES this thing but only if I just tie it on both sides of the car seat rather than actually wrapping the spiral as designed. When I use the spiral, it only covers maybe an 8 inch portion of the bar, and if I try to stretch it then the hanging toys don’t all hang evenly. Either way, the strings are too short for him to actually reach or play with the toys. However, when I tie it as shown in the video, he has a blast.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Baby loves to look at these toys while in the car seat! Great purchase and totally recommend. They make noise and play a song.
